<subSubSection id="10ED9AC52D7EFF92FFC8F977FECD0D22" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5848C94E2D7EFF93FFC8F977FBB40CDF" blockId="22.[151,1436,314,2029]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="6A83155C2D7EFF93FFC8F977FEE60DE1" bold="true" box="[199,325,1722,1747]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Discussion</emphasis>
. I have redescribed this species from the pair of specimens from Colima reported in 
<bibRefCitation id="3C66B4BF2D7EFF93FA13F976FEDD0DC4" author="Westcott" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Westcott, R. L. &amp; Hespenheide, H. A. (2006) The description of a new species of Agrilus Curtis, with distributional records and taxonomic and biological notes for Agrilinae and Trachyinae (Coleoptera: Buprestidae) of Mexico and Central America. Zootaxa, 1367, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="2006">
Westcott &amp; Hespenheide (
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FE37F913FED50DC4" box="[312,374,1758,1782]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. As interpreted here, this is a moderately variable Mexican species that may actually include more than a single species but does not include the Costa Rican 
<taxonomicName id="9FF7B2CD2D7EFF93FC69F8CCFBCF0C2B" authority="Obenberger" authorityName="Obenberger" box="[870,1132,1793,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kulagini">
<emphasis id="6A83155C2D7EFF93FC69F8CCFC420C2B" box="[870,993,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. kulagini</emphasis>
Obenberger
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="3C66B4BF2D7EFF93FBAEF8CCFAD70C2B" author="Hespenheide" box="[1185,1396,1793,1817]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Hespenheide, H. A. (1979) Nomenclatural notes on the Agrilinae (Coleoptera, Buprestidae): IV. Coleopterists Bulletin, 33, 105 - 120." type="journal article" year="1979">
Hespenheide 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FA37F8CCFAD70C2B" box="[1336,1396,1793,1817]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). A major surprise was the sexual difference in antennal structure, with the antennae of males serrate from antennomere 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FF98F88AFF060C6D" box="[151,165,1863,1887]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="4.0">4</number>
and those of females from antennomere 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FD78F88AFD2B0C6D" box="[631,648,1863,1887]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="5.0">5</number>
. This difference usually separate major species groups (Fisher 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FA5BF88AFA2C0C6D" box="[1364,1423,1863,1887]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1928.0">1928</number>
), although extreme sexual differences in antennal structure are known elsewhere in 
<taxonomicName id="9FF7B2CD2D7EFF93FB27F8A6FBD90CB1" box="[1064,1146,1899,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6A83155C2D7EFF93FB27F8A6FBD90CB1" box="[1064,1146,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Agrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="6A83155C2D7EFF93FB87F8A1FB130CB1" box="[1160,1200,1900,1923]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">e.g.</emphasis>
, in the 
<taxonomicName id="9FF7B2CD2D7EFF93FA0CF8A6FEB80C94" authority="Waterhouse" authorityName="Waterhouse" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus">
<emphasis id="6A83155C2D7EFF93FA0CF8A6FA3F0CB1" box="[1283,1436,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. antennatus</emphasis>
Waterhouse
</taxonomicName>
species group. The specimen from 
<quantity id="9F0F64AB2D7EFF93FDB7F843FCA10C94" box="[696,770,1934,1958]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
NE Oaxaca is included with reservations. Males measure 
<quantity id="9F0F64AB2D7EFF93FF98F87CFE990CFB" box="[151,314,1969,1993]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="4.9" valueMax="5.4" valueMin="4.4">4.40–5.40 mm</quantity>
long (mean = 
<quantity id="9F0F64AB2D7EFF93FED1F87CFDE60CFB" box="[478,581,1969,1993]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.98" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="4.98">4.98 mm</quantity>
, n = 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FD72F87CFD2F0CFB" box="[637,652,1969,1993]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="5.0">5</number>
), females measure 
<quantity id="9F0F64AB2D7EFF93FC69F87CFBAA0CFB" box="[870,1033,1969,1993]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="5.25" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="4.8">4.80–5.70 mm</quantity>
long (mean = 
<quantity id="9F0F64AB2D7EFF93FBA2F87CFAB00CFB" box="[1197,1299,1969,1993]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="5.24">5.24 mm</quantity>
, n = 
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FA44F87CFAF80CFB" box="[1355,1371,1969,1993]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="5.0">5</number>
). The recently described 
<taxonomicName id="9FF7B2CD2D7EFF93FE65F819FD4A0CDE" authority="Curletti &amp; Brule (2011)" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Brule" authorityYear="2011" box="[362,745,2004,2028]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristani">
<emphasis id="6A83155C2D7EFF93FE65F819FE790CDE" box="[362,474,2004,2028]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. tristani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3C66B4BF2D7EFF93FEEEF819FD4A0CDE" author="Curletti" box="[481,745,2004,2028]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Curletti, G. &amp; S. Brule. (2011) Les Genres Agrilus, Agriloides et Autarcontes en Guyane Francaise (Coleoptera Buprestidae). Collection ex Natura Volume 2, 84 pp. Magellanes, Andresy, France." type="book" year="2011">
Curletti &amp; Brûlé (
<number id="EE3FDB692D7EFF93FDA7F819FD410CDE" box="[680,738,2004,2028]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also belongs in this group.
</paragraph>
